Q:

How to append the value of a string to another string in an array?

I am trying to do this:

Find all the strings that start with "c" and append them to each other string.

I tried to write this:
var strings = ['C', 'c'];
var arr = strings.map(function (string) {
  return string.split('c');
});

var arr = ["C", "c"];
console.log(arr);

But it doesn't append the value of the string "C".

A:

You have to specify the delimiter in the method containing the split function:

const strings = ['C', 'c'];
const arr = strings.map(function (string) {
  return string.split('c');
});

const arr = ["C", "c"];
console.log(arr);

console.log(arr.join(', '));

Note:

There is more clarity in the answer, using a for, instead of a for-each

